{
  "info": {
    "name": "Setu SE Assignment",
    "description": "Payment reconciliation service — 5 endpoints covering ingestion, transaction lookup, and reconciliation views.\n\nSet the `baseUrl` collection variable to either your deployed URL or `http://127.0.0.1:8000`. Every request uses `{{baseUrl}}` so you can switch environments without touching individual requests.\n\nSuggested run order (tells the full story):\n1. `Health → Health check`\n2. `Events → Ingest new event` (201 Created)\n3. `Events → Idempotency replay` (200 OK — same event_id, no duplication)\n4. `Events → Settled follow-up` (lifecycle → current_status flips to settled)\n5. `Events → Out-of-order initiated` (late event must NOT regress status)\n6. `Events → Discrepancy seed (failed)` + `(settled)` — sets up the discrepancy demo\n7. `Transactions → List all` / filters / sorts / pagination\n8. `Transactions → Detail` (shows event history for the txn above)\n9. `Reconciliation → Summary` — per merchant / date / combined\n10. `Reconciliation → Discrepancies` — conflicting_events surfaces the seeded pair",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000",
      "description": "Base URL. Override with your deployed URL (e.g. https://setu-se.onrender.com) for production testing."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Root — sanity check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": [""]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Health — DB reachability",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Events — ingestion",
      "description": "POST /events — idempotent event ingestion.\n\nFirst call returns 201 Created. Replaying the same event_id returns 200 OK with status=duplicate (no DB mutation). The service also enforces status precedence so late-arriving events never regress a transaction's current_status.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Ingest new event (201 Created)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('status=accepted', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('accepted'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event_id\": \"b768e3a7-9eb3-4603-b21c-a54cc95661bc\",\n  \"event_type\": \"payment_initiated\",\n  \"transaction_id\": \"2f86e94c-239c-4302-9874-75f28e3474ee\",\n  \"merchant_id\": \"merchant_2\",\n  \"merchant_name\": \"FreshBasket\",\n  \"amount\": 15248.29,\n  \"currency\": \"INR\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-01-08T12:11:58.085567+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/events",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["events"]
            },
            "description": "First call for this event_id — server records the event and creates/updates the transaction."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Idempotency replay (200 OK, duplicate)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('status=duplicate', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('duplicate'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event_id\": \"b768e3a7-9eb3-4603-b21c-a54cc95661bc\",\n  \"event_type\": \"payment_initiated\",\n  \"transaction_id\": \"2f86e94c-239c-4302-9874-75f28e3474ee\",\n  \"merchant_id\": \"merchant_2\",\n  \"merchant_name\": \"FreshBasket\",\n  \"amount\": 15248.29,\n  \"currency\": \"INR\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-01-08T12:11:58.085567+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/events",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["events"]
            },
            "description": "Identical event_id to the request above. Server returns 200 with status=duplicate — no double-count, no second DB write."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Settled follow-up (lifecycle progression)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event_id\": \"99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999991\",\n  \"event_type\": \"settled\",\n  \"transaction_id\": \"2f86e94c-239c-4302-9874-75f28e3474ee\",\n  \"merchant_id\": \"merchant_2\",\n  \"merchant_name\": \"FreshBasket\",\n  \"amount\": 15248.29,\n  \"currency\": \"INR\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-01-09T10:00:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/events",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["events"]
            },
            "description": "Second event on the same transaction — flips current_status to 'settled'."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Out-of-order initiated (no regression)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event_id\": \"99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999992\",\n  \"event_type\": \"payment_initiated\",\n  \"transaction_id\": \"2f86e94c-239c-4302-9874-75f28e3474ee\",\n  \"merchant_id\": \"merchant_2\",\n  \"merchant_name\": \"FreshBasket\",\n  \"amount\": 15248.29,\n  \"currency\": \"INR\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-01-07T00:00:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/events",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["events"]
            },
            "description": "Late-arriving 'initiated' event for an already-settled transaction. The event is recorded in the log for audit, but current_status stays 'settled' because the precedence rule (settled > initiated) prevents regression."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Discrepancy seed — payment_failed",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event_id\": \"99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999993\",\n  \"event_type\": \"payment_failed\",\n  \"transaction_id\": \"2ea525e0-f152-485f-9f6b-e5c7ca54f1f0\",\n  \"merchant_id\": \"merchant_1\",\n  \"merchant_name\": \"QuickMart\",\n  \"amount\": 9169.41,\n  \"currency\": \"INR\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-01-08T13:30:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/events",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["events"]
            },
            "description": "Half of the contradictory pair. Run together with the next request to seed /reconciliation/discrepancies."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Discrepancy seed — settled (contradicts)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event_id\": \"99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999994\",\n  \"event_type\": \"settled\",\n  \"transaction_id\": \"2ea525e0-f152-485f-9f6b-e5c7ca54f1f0\",\n  \"merchant_id\": \"merchant_1\",\n  \"merchant_name\": \"QuickMart\",\n  \"amount\": 9169.41,\n  \"currency\": \"INR\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-01-08T16:00:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/events",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["events"]
            },
            "description": "The 'settled' event that contradicts the 'payment_failed' above. After both are ingested, this transaction appears in /reconciliation/discrepancies under conflicting_events."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "422 — negative amount",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event_id\": \"11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111\",\n  \"event_type\": \"payment_initiated\",\n  \"transaction_id\": \"22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222\",\n  \"merchant_id\": \"merchant_2\",\n  \"merchant_name\": \"FreshBasket\",\n  \"amount\": -100.00,\n  \"currency\": \"INR\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-01-08T00:00:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/events",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["events"]
            },
            "description": "Validation rejects amounts <= 0 at the schema layer."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "422 — unknown event_type",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event_id\": \"11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111112\",\n  \"event_type\": \"NOT_A_REAL_TYPE\",\n  \"transaction_id\": \"22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222\",\n  \"merchant_id\": \"merchant_2\",\n  \"merchant_name\": \"FreshBasket\",\n  \"amount\": 100.00,\n  \"currency\": \"INR\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-01-08T00:00:00+00:00\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/events",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["events"]
            },
            "description": "Validation rejects event_type values outside the allowed enum."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Transactions — list",
      "description": "GET /transactions — filter, sort, paginate. Filters are AND-composed. Sort accepts initiated_at | amount | current_status | updated_at with optional '-' prefix for descending.",
